import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['fertility'] = pd.to_numeric(data['fertility'], errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="country", y="fertility", data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['pop', 'life_expect'])
    sns.scatterplot(x='pop', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between population and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pop'] = data['pop'].astype(int)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='pop', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different clusters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['cluster'] = data['cluster'].astype(str)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='cluster', y='life_expect', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average life expectancy of each cluster?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
